dcterms:description: The JetClass dataset is a large-scale jet dataset containing 125M jets from ten different types of particles, including light quarks, gluons, various decay modes of top quarks, and Higgs bosons. It is used to train an anomaly detection model on q/g (QCD) jets and evaluate performance on other processes.
dcterms:title: JetClass Dataset
